article.headline: N.Carolina A&T 70, Maryland-Eastern Shore 57
article.story: PRINCESS ANNE, Md. (AP) -- Jason Wills scored 20 points to lead North Carolina A&T to a 70-57 victory over Maryland-Eastern Shore on Saturday. Wills led four Aggies in double figures. Walter Booth and Steven Rush contributed 11 points each and Angelo Hernandez added another 10 for N. Carolina A & T (10-12, 6-4 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). Ed Tyson led Md.-Eastern Shore (3-19, 0-10) with 20 points on 6-13 shooting from 3-point range. Danijel Krleski added nine points off the bench for the Hawks. McMillion and Krleski combined for nine points to close the gap to four with about seven minutes to go. But Wills bounced back in the closing minutes by scoring nine points to seal the victory.
